  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Is it possible to check and limit the number of shared peers a node has with it's other peers?  It's sub-optimal to allow you and your peer to connect to mostly the other nodes.  I'm not where the go code for peer authorization lives, but this could potentially improve propagation times by reducing redundant connections. \n\nMaybe it already does this in some fashion?\n",
